								<div class="newsitem">
									<h3 class="title"><a href="/star-wars-the-old-republic/columns/gear-progression-goes-rng-with-eternal-thrones-galactic-command-1000011252">Gear Progression Goes RNG with Eternal Throne’s Galactic Command </a></h3>

									<div class="news_newspost"><a href="/star-wars-the-old-republic/columns/gear-progression-goes-rng-with-eternal-thrones-galactic-command-1000011252"><img src="http://images.mmorpg.com/images/heroes/features/11252.jpg" width="466" border="0" alt="Gear Progression Goes RNG with Eternal Throne’s Galactic Command  - Star Wars: The Old Republic Columns" style="padding-bottom:5px;" /></a><p>BioWare's latest live stream event detailed the new Galactic Command system coming to Star Wars: The Old Republic with the release of the Knights of the Eternal Throne expansion this December. The structural changes made to gear progression with this system are set to have a far-reaching impact on the game, and the community isn't exactly too happy about it.</p></div>
